## Server vs Client Component Decision

| Need | Server Component | Client Component |
|------|:---:|:---:|
| Fetch data from DB / API | ✅ | ❌ avoid |
| Access env vars (server-only) | ✅ | ❌ |
| Use `useState`, `useEffect`, hooks | ❌ | ✅ |
| Handle click/change events | ❌ | ✅ |
| Browser APIs (localStorage, window) | ❌ | ✅ |
| Import heavy client libs (charts, editors) | ❌ prefer | ✅ |
| Stream large content | ✅ | ❌ |

### Pattern: Push interactivity to leaves
```tsx
// app/users/page.tsx — Server Component
async function UsersPage() {
  const users = await db.users.findMany(); // Direct DB access!
  return (
    <section>
      <h1>Users</h1>
      {users.map(u => (
        <UserCard key={u.id} user={u} />  {/* Server Component */}
      ))}
    </section>
  );
}

// components/UserCard.tsx — Still Server (no 'use client')
async function UserCard({ user }: { user: User }) {
  return (
    <article>
      <h2>{user.name}</h2>
      <DeleteButton userId={user.id} /> {/* Client Component at the leaf */}
    </article>
  );
}

// components/DeleteButton.tsx — Client Component
'use client';
function DeleteButton({ userId }: { userId: string }) {
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();
  return <button onClick={() => startTransition(() => deleteUser(userId))}>Delete</button>;
}
```

**Rules:**
- Never lift 'use client' to a layout or page unless the entire tree needs it
- Pass Server Component output as `children` prop into Client Components to keep the tree partially server-rendered

## Server Actions Pattern

### actions/users.ts
```ts
'use server';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';
import { z } from 'zod';

const schema = z.object({ name: z.string().min(2), email: z.string().email() });

export async function createUser(prevState: unknown, formData: FormData) {
  const parsed = schema.safeParse(Object.fromEntries(formData));
  if (!parsed.success) {
    return { errors: parsed.error.flatten().fieldErrors };
  }
  await db.users.create({ data: parsed.data });
  revalidatePath('/users');
  redirect('/users');
}
```

### Form with useActionState
```tsx
'use client';
import { useActionState } from 'react';
import { createUser } from '@/actions/users';

export function CreateUserForm() {
  const [state, action, isPending] = useActionState(createUser, null);
  return (
    <form action={action}>
      <input name="name" />
      {state?.errors?.name && <p>{state.errors.name[0]}</p>}
      <input name="email" type="email" />
      {state?.errors?.email && <p>{state.errors.email[0]}</p>}
      <button type="submit" disabled={isPending}>
        {isPending ? 'Creating...' : 'Create'}
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

**Security rules:**
- Always validate inputs in the Server Action — client can send anything
- Use `cookies().get()` to check auth inside Server Actions — never trust client-passed userId
- Never expose internal DB errors in the returned state

## Next.js Data Fetching & Cache Control

```ts
// 1. Static — cached indefinitely (default)
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/products');

// 2. No cache — opt into dynamic rendering
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/cart', { cache: 'no-store' });

// 3. Time-based revalidation — ISR
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/products', {
  next: { revalidate: 3600 } // revalidate every hour
});

// 4. Tag-based revalidation — on-demand ISR
const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/products', {
  next: { tags: ['products'] }
});
// Then in a Server Action:
import { revalidateTag } from 'next/cache';
revalidateTag('products'); // invalidate all fetches with this tag
```

### ORM / non-fetch data (Prisma, Drizzle)
```ts
import { unstable_cache } from 'next/cache';

const getProducts = unstable_cache(
  async () => db.products.findMany(),
  ['products-list'],           // cache key
  { tags: ['products'], revalidate: 3600 }
);
```

### Route segment config
```ts
// page.tsx or layout.tsx
export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'; // never cache this segment
export const revalidate = 60;           // revalidate every 60s
export const fetchCache = 'force-no-store';
```

**Rules:**
- Prefer tagged caches over time-based — trigger revalidation precisely on data change
- Dynamic rendering costs cold-start latency — use static + revalidation where possible
- Parallel fetch independent data with `Promise.all()` in Server Components

## Streaming with Suspense in Next.js App Router

```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <main>
      {/* Fast — renders immediately */}
      <StaticHeader />

      {/* Slow — streams in when ready */}
      <Suspense fallback={<MetricsSkeleton />}>
        <MetricsPanel />  {/* async Server Component */}
      </Suspense>

      <Suspense fallback={<TableSkeleton />}>
        <RecentOrdersTable />  {/* async Server Component */}
      </Suspense>
    </main>
  );
}

// MetricsPanel.tsx — async Server Component
async function MetricsPanel() {
  const metrics = await db.metrics.aggregate({ /* slow query */ });
  return <div>{/* render metrics */}</div>;
}
```

### loading.tsx — automatic Suspense boundary
```tsx
// app/dashboard/loading.tsx — wraps the entire route segment
export default function Loading() {
  return <DashboardSkeleton />;
}
```

**Rules:**
- Each independently-slow component gets its own `<Suspense>` boundary
- Use skeleton components as fallbacks — not spinners — to prevent layout shift
- Don't `await` multiple fetches sequentially — use `Promise.all()` for parallel

## Next.js Metadata API

### Static metadata
```ts
// app/layout.tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next';

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: { default: 'My App', template: '%s | My App' },
  description: 'Default description',
  metadataBase: new URL('https://example.com'),
  openGraph: {
    type: 'website',
    siteName: 'My App',
    images: [{ url: '/og-default.jpg', width: 1200, height: 630 }],
  },
  twitter: { card: 'summary_large_image' },
  robots: { index: true, follow: true },
};
```

### Dynamic metadata (generateMetadata)
```ts
// app/products/[id]/page.tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next';

export async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: { id: string } }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const product = await getProduct(params.id);
  if (!product) return { title: 'Not Found' };

  return {
    title: product.name,
    description: product.description,
    openGraph: {
      title: product.name,
      description: product.description,
      images: [{ url: product.imageUrl, width: 1200, height: 630 }],
    },
  };
}
```

### Dynamic OG image (opengraph-image.tsx)
```tsx
// app/products/[id]/opengraph-image.tsx
import { ImageResponse } from 'next/og';

export const runtime = 'edge';
export const size = { width: 1200, height: 630 };

export default async function OGImage({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const product = await getProduct(params.id);
  return new ImageResponse(
    <div style={{ fontSize: 64, background: 'white', padding: 64 }}>{product.name}</div>
  );
}
```

## Next.js Middleware

```ts
// middleware.ts (project root)
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import type { NextRequest } from 'next/server';
import { verifyJwt } from '@/lib/auth';

export async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const { pathname } = request.nextUrl;

  // Public paths — no auth needed
  const isPublic = pathname.startsWith('/login') ||
                   pathname.startsWith('/register') ||
                   pathname.startsWith('/api/auth');
  if (isPublic) return NextResponse.next();

  // Verify JWT from cookie
  const token = request.cookies.get('accessToken')?.value;
  if (!token) {
    const loginUrl = new URL('/login', request.url);
    loginUrl.searchParams.set('from', pathname);
    return NextResponse.redirect(loginUrl);
  }

  try {
    const payload = await verifyJwt(token);
    // Forward user info to headers for Server Components
    const response = NextResponse.next();
    response.headers.set('x-user-id', payload.sub);
    return response;
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/login', request.url));
  }
}

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|.*\.(?:svg|png|jpg|gif|webp)).*)'],
};
```

**Rules:**
- Middleware runs on the Edge runtime — no Node.js APIs, no Prisma
- Use `matcher` to exclude static assets — don't run on every request
- Heavy auth logic (DB lookups) belongs in Server Components or Route Handlers — middleware should only check tokens

## next/image Best Practices

```tsx
import Image from 'next/image';

// Hero image — eager load, high priority
<Image
  src="/hero.jpg"
  alt="Hero banner showing our product"
  width={1200}
  height={630}
  priority            // preloads — use for LCP images only
  fetchPriority="high"
  quality={85}
/>

// Content image — lazy by default
<Image
  src={user.avatarUrl}
  alt={`${user.name} profile picture`}
  width={48}
  height={48}
  className="rounded-full"
/>

// Fill a container (replaces background-image)
<div className="relative aspect-video">
  <Image
    src={product.imageUrl}
    alt={product.name}
    fill
    sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw"  // IMPORTANT: helps browser pick correct size
    className="object-cover"
  />
</div>
```

### Remote images — configure domains
```ts
// next.config.ts
const config = {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      { protocol: 'https', hostname: 'cdn.example.com', pathname: '/images/**' }
    ],
  },
};
```

**Rules:**
- Always provide `alt` — empty string only for decorative images
- Always provide `sizes` when using `fill` — missing `sizes` downloads the largest image
- Only use `priority` on LCP images — using it everywhere defeats the purpose

## Route Handlers in App Router

```ts
// app/api/webhooks/stripe/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server';
import Stripe from 'stripe';

const stripe = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY!);

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  const body = await request.text(); // raw body for signature verification
  const sig = request.headers.get('stripe-signature')!;

  let event: Stripe.Event;
  try {
    event = stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(body, sig, process.env.STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET!);
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Invalid signature' }, { status: 400 });
  }

  switch (event.type) {
    case 'payment_intent.succeeded':
      await handlePaymentSucceeded(event.data.object);
      break;
  }

  return NextResponse.json({ received: true });
}
```

### Dynamic route handler
```ts
// app/api/users/[id]/route.ts
export async function GET(request: NextRequest, { params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const user = await db.users.findUnique({ where: { id: params.id } });
  if (!user) return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Not found' }, { status: 404 });
  return NextResponse.json(user);
}

export async function DELETE(request: NextRequest, { params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  await db.users.delete({ where: { id: params.id } });
  return new NextResponse(null, { status: 204 });
}
```

**Server Action vs Route Handler:**
- Own UI mutation → Server Action
- Third-party webhooks, binary data, streaming → Route Handler
- Public REST API → Route Handler

## next/font Optimization

```ts
// app/fonts.ts
import { Inter, Playfair_Display } from 'next/font/google';
import localFont from 'next/font/local';

export const inter = Inter({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap',
  variable: '--font-inter', // expose as CSS var
});

export const playfair = Playfair_Display({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  weight: ['400', '700'],
  style: ['normal', 'italic'],
  variable: '--font-playfair',
  display: 'swap',
});

// Self-hosted font
export const brandFont = localFont({
  src: './fonts/Brand-Regular.woff2',
  variable: '--font-brand',
  display: 'swap',
});
```

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { inter, playfair } from './fonts';

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className={`${inter.variable} ${playfair.variable}`}>
      <body className={inter.className}>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

```css
/* Use variables in CSS */
h1, h2 { font-family: var(--font-playfair); }
body    { font-family: var(--font-inter); }
```

**Rules:**
- Max 2 font families per project — each additional font is a performance cost
- Use `display: 'swap'` to avoid invisible text while loading
- Specify `subsets` — reduces file size significantly
- Self-host with `localFont` if GDPR compliance or offline support is needed
